          "answerType"       :"freeText",
          "required"         :false,
          "answerPlaceholder":"Your thoughts...",
          "sampleAnswer"     :"Three things change immediately. First, they become aware of their nakedness and feel shame — contrasting sharply with the "no shame" of Genesis 2:25. Second, they attempt to cover themselves with fig leaves — self-protection and concealment replace openness. Third, when they hear God, they hide — the relationship that was previously characterised by ease and freedom has become something they now fear. The man explicitly says he was afraid. Shame, hiding, and fear are the immediate fruits of the sin.",
