        {
          "elementId"        :"ch03-el19",
          "type"             :"question",
          "format"           :"plainText",
          "question"         :"Why do you think shame and hiding are the first responses to sin?",
          "linkedPassage"    :"Genesis 3:7–10",
          "answerType"       :"freeText",
          "required"         :false,
          "answerPlaceholder":"Your thoughts...",
          "sampleAnswer"     :"Shame arises because they know they have done something wrong — the knowledge of good and evil they sought has arrived, but not as the upgrade they expected. Instead of wisdom, it brings self-awareness of failure. Hiding follows naturally from shame: if you feel exposed and guilty, the instinct is to avoid the one who knows, especially if you fear their judgment. The relationship with God, which was once easy and open, is now experienced as threatening. Shame and hiding are the internal experience of a broken relationship.",
