          "format"       :"HTML",
          "text"         :"By Genesis 6, the world has changed beyond recognition from the good creation of Genesis 1. Sin has spread across generations, grown more violent, more brazen, more widespread. The question that Genesis now forces is: what does a holy God do with a world that has become thoroughly corrupt? The flood is the answer — and it is deeply uncomfortable, and deeply important, in equal measure.<br><br>But the flood is not only a story about judgment. It is also a story about grace.",
