          "text"         :"One of the most valuable things to do with the whole of Genesis 1-12 is to ask: what kind of God has been revealed here? The picture is rich and multi-layered.<br><br>He is the Creator who speaks the world into existence and calls it good. He is personal – close enough to form a man from dust and breathe life into him. He is holy, and takes sin seriously enough to act against it. He is merciful, covering shame, protecting Cain, saving Noah, calling Abram. He is faithful, making promises and keeping them. He is sovereign, overseeing the rise and fall of nations, working His purposes through ordinary and unlikely people.",
