          "text"         :"Genesis is equally honest about humanity. We are made in God’s image – which means we have real dignity, real purpose, real capacity for relationship with God. And we are fallen – which means we are prone to doubt, to self-assertion, to hiding, to blame, to the slow drift away from God that the whole of Genesis 3-11 traces in painful detail.<br><br>Neither of these truths can be held without the other. To know only our dignity leads to pride. To know only our fallenness leads to despair. Genesis holds them together, and in doing so, it tells the truth.",
